title: Episode 183: Overcoming Insecure Attachment w/ Tracy Crossley
description:
Show Notes:
Are you a love addict? [04:30]
The book that lead both Robbie & Tracy to explore their attachment styles? [04:46]
The process of becoming addicted to someone… [07:46]
Is it possible to have both anxious and avoidant attachment styles? [09:40]
Why attachment issues bring up scarcity and how to solve this… [15:03]
How to deal with a narcissist and the pros and cons of using these labels… [17:01]
Are “The 5 Love Languages” bullshit or legit? [22:51]
How your attachment style affects you in the workplace/career? [24:35]
What to do if you’ve come to the realization that you’re addicted to either a toxic partner or addicted to your job? [27:23]
Imposter syndrome and how to recover from it? [31:05]
The truth about choosing and setting healthy boundaries… [32:13]
What if you’re detached from your emotions and you’re not sure what you’re even feeling… how can understand what’s going on and stop avoiding your own emotions and pushing people away? [37:30]
The “Pyramid of Beliefs” which allows you to deconstruct unconscious patterns of listening to your own bullshit stories… [41:15]
A case study of an insecurely attached client who’s dating a webcam model and dealing with a toxic relationship… [43:30 – 51:00]

Links:
TracyCrossley.com
Freedom From Attachment Podcast

I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.
